Text.Value: All set, are ya?
Oh, you're one of those types. Rude as you are sneaky.
I need something potent. What do you have?
My business is slinging tankards, not hoarding secrets. I'd like to keep it that way.
Cold feet, eh? Don't blame you. Left my first wife at the altar. Some flavours just aren't worth tasting.
Rustled Irenya's feathers, eh? Well, no harm done. Her moneymaker catches more Fist than a frog catches flies.

EditorData.NodeContext: Loud and boisterous but never obnoxious.

Text.Value: You got it - but the new hooch is off-limits. Can't have the Mamzell leaping down my throat if I go burning yours.
I'll take my chances on the hooch.
Leave.
Show me what you have.
Have a look.
I'd like to see what else you have.
Now, that there's a face I'd remember if I'd seen it. Welcome to Sharess' Caress!

EditorData.NodeContext: Loud and boisterous but never obnoxious.

Text.Value: That rough, eh? Well you can't say I didn't warn you. Buyer beware, and all that junk.
Damn - the man knows what he wants!
Damn - the gal knows what she wants!
Damn - this one knows what they want!
Never again. What in the Hells did you put in there?
I bet a barkeep in this place hears all sorts of stories.
Pinch of this, smidgen of that. Least you still got your tongue. Last customer wasn't so lucky.
But you poke some folk hard enough, they're bound to squeal. And Mamzell Amira there looks about ready to burst.
I don't know about that, chum. Hoots' Hooch packs a stronger wallop than all ten of my knuckles.
You fancy another? Or just hankerin' for chat?
Could beef you up, sharpen your tongue - or knock you out cold. No telling 'til the first drop hits your gullet.
Pleasure to serve.
What can Hoots do you for, stranger? You got a taste for ale, I reckon. Or maybe -

EditorData.NodeContext: Starts to recommend her newest brew...

Text.Value: The Flaming Fist should lock you up for selling the stuff.
Sharess' Caress? The Mamzell's brainchild. 'Wet your tongue, soak your skin, scratch your itch.'
What's the story of this place?
On second thought, I'll pass.
Press your belly to the bar, chum.
Try something else? Or just feeling things out?
Looking for flavour to savour? Perhaps -

EditorData.logicalname: HasMet, didn't ask about potent drink

Text.Value: Hells yeah, and blessings to the drunken god!
Your new brew sounds potent. I'll give that a try.
Well? Whaddya think, now you had a swig of the hooch?
First one's on the house. So don't come bawling to me if your big toes fall off or your tongue coils in a knot!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Leans forward, gives you the drink just below camera, and it goes into player inventory.

Text.Value: Look, we both know how this works - rumours, jobs, anything - I want the details.
Ah, forget it. My new brew could drop you in the wink of a spectator's eye.

EditorData.NodeContext: ...and then changes her mind. But cheeky about it.

Text.Value: Get the attention you want - and avoid the attention you don't.
It's godsdamned good, is what I think.
I'd rather not talk about it.
A manip's the one who brought me the fixings! A Fist's stomach's stronger than a mountain troll on a bender.
Try Hoots' Hooch. Cuts real deep.

Synopsis: Bartender in Sharess' caress, vendor for drinks and such.
